to remain autonom the fact that the ottoman empir wa the longest live in recent histori mai be attribut to these freedom despit the lack of ani written constitut the first attempt to creat a written constitut occur in and although the document adopt dure these two attempt remain in forc onli temporarili thei provid the basic element of a constitut the constitut wa the first legal document to forc a parliament and the right of elect to share the sovereignti of the emperor the constitut of place some addit limit on the emperor while increas the power of the parliament and the govern the first world war brought the ottoman empir to an end by the occup of istanbul the parliament wa dissolv and the constitut wa abolish the member of parliament were sent to exil to an island by the occupi forc dure the independ war the turkish grand nation assembl held their first meet on april to serv as the legisl bodi of the new turkish state thi assembl prepar the new legal structur of the turkish republ the new republ wa proclaim on octob and the new constitut wa adopt in that constitut serv as the legal backbon of todai s modern turkish republ in turkei adopt a multi parti polit system the constitut of wa replac by other in and all three constitut of the republ have been base on the principl of parliamentari democraci human right nation sovereignti divis of power privat ownership and secular major principl of the constitut the constitut with articl establish the structur of the republ within the follow principl the turkish republ is a democrat secular and social state govern by law it should be govern to maintain public peac nation solidar justic human right and the object of ataturk the languag of the state is turkish sovereignti is vest in the nation without ani condit or restrict sovereignti is exercis by organ author by the nation legisl power is carri by the parliament elect by the nation thi power cannot be deleg transfer to ani on els execut power is exercis by the presid and council of minist judici power is exercis by the independ court on behalf of the turkish nation all individu ar equal irrespect of languag race religion color sex or polit belief law cannot be contradict those principl state in the constitut structur of the state in accord with the constitut the structur of the state is base on the principl of divis of power to creat a balanc and self control system the power is divid into legisl power execut power and judici power balanc to secur freedom and power to control each other self control a legisl power the turkish grand nation assembl is a parliament with on hous elect by the nation for a term of five year to exercis legisl power on behalf of the nation the basic function of thi assembl ar to adopt to amend or to repeal law to approv or to dismiss the council of minist to supervis and to question minist or the council of minist to debat to amend and to approv annual budget to ratifi intern agreement to grant amnesti or pardon member of parliament do not have ani liabil for their word either oral or written dure the cours of their legisl duti the countri is divid into constitu the number of repres of each is calcul accord to it popul everi turkish citizen over the ag of twenti on can vote elect ar supervis by the suprem council of elect which solv all disput or appeal in each provinc the local board of elect run and control the elect under the supervis and guidelin of the suprem council member of the council and board ar elect among independ judg b execut power the presid of the republ is the head of state not the head of govern as in the unit state the main function of the presid ar to repres the state and the countri to insur the implement of the constitut to coordin legisl judici and execut function act as the suprem command of the arm forc to ratifi law and govern decre the presid is elect by the grand nation assembl for a period of seven year the presid mai ratifi or return the law for a second debat mai call for a 